text: Must be the most expensive Nasi Padang in SG. Loose cup of rice (probably half only) Small piece of chicken, 1.5 hotdog (4 cut pieces) and a small amount of veggie. SGD 10.50. Also very inconsistent, I've had the same combination for SGD 9. Are they just guessing the price? It tastes ok, not great. But the price is just way to ex.

We often to buy the food in here for lunch or dinner cause their food is yummy, the price is good, oh and if you want to have breakfast, they serve very good nasi lemak. The staff are friendly, patience and helpful. I love their black squid, ayam goreng, fried fish and sambal balacan, so good! The place is clean, cold, it's new and cozzy after renovation.
We had the most heartiest brekkie ever. The Mee Siam bowl is so big portion. The bowl of longtong is tasty. Importantly the price is very affordable.  ComeÂ² and do have a meal here.
Super yummy, Every bite was heaven! Very impressive, really must try!
